# Nectar SDK - Multi-orientation rangefinder test parameters
#
# Forward/back rangefinders fed by the iris_with_rangefinders Gazebo model
# (rng_2/rng_3). ArduPilot emits one DISTANCE_SENSOR per instance with
# id = instance and orientation = RNGFNDx_ORIENT, which the SDK exposes through
# drone.distance_sensors / drone.get_distance().
#
# The downward rangefinder (RNGFND1, id 0, orientation DOWN) stays on the analog
# SITL sonar configured in gazebo.parm. On the ground the airframe is only ~0.2 m
# tall, so a downward GPU lidar sits under the body and reads below its minimum
# range; the analog sonar reports vehicle height above terrain reliably, which is
# what the SDK uses as an altitude reference. The Gazebo down lidar is still
# produced (rng_1) but the FCU's downward reading comes from the sonar.
#
# Load after gazebo.parm:
#   start_sitl.sh --gazebo --params nectar/simulation/params/rangefinder_test.parm
#
# ORIENT values are ArduPilot Rotation enum (= MAV_SENSOR_ORIENTATION):
#   0 = forward, 4 = YAW_180 (back), 25 = PITCH_270 (down)

# Forward (rng_2) -> DISTANCE_SENSOR id 1, orientation FORWARD
RNGFND2_TYPE    100
RNGFND2_ORIENT  0
RNGFND2_MIN     0.10
RNGFND2_MAX     40.0

# Back (rng_3) -> DISTANCE_SENSOR id 2, orientation BACK
RNGFND3_TYPE    100
RNGFND3_ORIENT  4
RNGFND3_MIN     0.10
RNGFND3_MAX     40.0
